      "themeTokens": "Semantic color token mappings for light and dark modes. Each token pairs a UI role (like 'page background' or 'heading text') with the Tailwind classes to use in each mode. Components reference these roles instead of hardcoding colors.",
      "componentMappings": "Per-component class transformation guide showing exactly which Tailwind classes change when adding dual-mode support. Each entry lists the file path, the current dark-only classes, and the new classes with light defaults plus dark: variants.",
      "foucPrevention": "The inline script that runs before first paint to detect the user's system color scheme preference and apply the .dark class to the HTML element, preventing a flash of the wrong theme."
    },
    "relationships": [
      "ThemeTokens define the color contract â€” every component's classes derive from these semantic roles",
      "ComponentMappings reference ThemeTokens to show the concrete class changes per file",
      "FoucPrevention ensures the correct theme token set is active before any component renders"
    ]
  },

